     After `[0m[2mawait asyncio.sleep([0m[2m0.02)[0m[2m`, the[0m[2m check[0m[2m-and-mod[0m[2mify runs[0m[2m without yielding. So[0m[2m no[0m[2m,[0m[2m `decrement()`[0m[2m can[0m[2m't make[0m[2m stock go negative by[0m[2m itself. But the[0m[2m problem statement[0m[2m says inventory[0m[2m can[0m[2m go negative. Let[0m[2m me think...[0m[2m
     
     If[0m[2m `[0m[2mde[0m[2mcrement()` has[0m[2m a[0m[2m lock-[0m[2mprotected check[0m[2m,[0m[2m it can't[0m[2m go negative. But[0m[2m without a lock,[0m[2m could[0m[2m interle[0m[2maving cause[0m[2m issues? In[0m[2m single[0m[2m-threaded asyncio,[0m[2m after the await[0m[2m, execution[0m[2m is sequential[0m[2m. So `de[0m[2mcrement()` is safe[0m[2m.
     
